{
  "stem": "11611.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were similar transactions with certain Czech Jews who had large holdings in the Sudeten area of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH] and [GERMAN] families were notorious for owning large tracts of soft coal, so-called brown coal.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were very well to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were Jews, but they were very Germanized too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, this was a German section of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "German was their language.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Their contacts were all German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They knew that they were in good standing during the Nazi period, though, and these families ultimately wound up in New York City, getting some money out because they negotiated more favorably with some of the Nazi hierarchy.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think particularly, they knew Goering or someone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they came out alive and with some property.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The primary charge against the Dresdner Bank was grabbing Jewish properties before or after the owners were murdered, you know, accessories to murder and theft.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These are war crimes under the Hague Conventions, particularly for properties outside of Germany, which was the real focus-- Czech properties, Dutch property, French property.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A second charge had nothing to do with Jews because they did exactly the same thing with Dutch, Belgians, and Czechs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't care who owned the property.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the property they wanted.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why did the Dresdner Bank want the property?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were middlemen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would bird-dog properties.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, they'd say, this is something we ought to grab, and deal with Kehrl in the Ministry of Economics, who would say yes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Why did they want to bird dog it?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "First, they were all Nazi patriots.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Second, when the properties were grabbed by Germans, they'd be placed with clients of the banks, and that was very desirable from the standpoint of making money.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
